
[1]scrap

   SCRAP, n. [from scrape.]

   1. A small piece; properly something scraped off, but used for any
   thing cut off; a fragment; a crumb; as scraps of meat.

   2. A part; a detached piece; as scraps of history or poetry; scraps of
   antiquity; scraps of authors.

   3. A small piece of paper. [If used for script, it is improper.]
     __________________________________________________________________

